    "text": "“A Stain on Red Sox Nation,” Leigh Montville’s review of Bill Nowlin’s “Tom Yawkey: Patriarch of the Boston Red Sox” is an excellent look at the plight of nonwhite players in Boston as well as the entire major leagues (Books, Feb. 3).\nHowever, the author says that baseball was a whites-only game at the major-league level until 1947. This is wrong. Many Native Americans played: Chief Bender, Chief Meyers, Louis Sockalexis, Jim Thorpe and more. Other nonwhites weren’t allowed to play.\n... ",
